# MV*

## MVC

Model-view-controller is the reference here :
![scheme](http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/a/a0/MVC-Process.svg)

## MVA

Model–view–adapter = MVP + multiple adapters between a view and model.

## MVP

Model-view-presenter is a variation of MVC but remove relation between view and model. It is often used in place of the MVC unknowingly.

## PAC

In contrast to MVC, PAC is used as a hierarchical structure.

## HMVC

Hierarchical model–view–controller (HMVC) is a variation of MVC similar to PAC published in 2000, 13 years later than PAC.
